item.title: AeroPress Coffee Filter Holder
item.description:
I love my AeroPress Coffee Maker but hated the box that held the filters. Every morning while half asleep I was fiddling with the original filter box to get out a single filter. I also didn't like the look of the box on an open counter next to all of my other beautiful coffee and espresso gear so I thought I would design something a pleasing to look at and easy to use.

I wanted an elegant way to organize and display my coffee area in the kitchen and make it easy to grab filters in the morning with no fuss. This simple design prints in 2 parts and snaps together easily with no glue.

  • Holds 500 filters. Design could be easily modified to hold more.
  • Print any color combination to make it unique.
  • No supports needed
  • No glue required, parts snap together easily

item.title: Terminal Tackle Box for Plano EDGE 3600 / 3700
item.description:
The Edge series of tackle boxes from Plano Molding are very high quality and have lots of configuration options. As a premium product, they can be a bit pricy however.

They offer a “Terminal Tackle” option in the 3600 and 3700 size boxes which add several removable boxes to the interior which help to keep small parts (such as hooks, sinkers, swivels, and split rings) from jumping from one compartment to the next or spilling out while the box is open.

My design adds similar functionality to the Plano EDGE Professional 3600 STD Box. I presume the inserts will work in the standard EDGE 3700 box as well. It seems likely that these are not direct replacements for the inserts in the EDGE 3600 or 3700 Terminal boxes, or the EDGE Professional 3700 Thin. I don't have any of those to test, and welcome your feedback if you do and are able to try it out!

item.title: MPCNC 65mm Spindelhalterung
item.description:
Spindelhalterung für eine 65mm "Chinaspindel".
Passt zur MPCNC mit 25mm Rohr.

Die Halterung wird direkt an die Z-Achse geschraubt, was mehr Stabilität und einen größeren Fräsbereich mit sich bringt.
Die Spindel liegt im Halter auf und wird mit 6x M5x30 Schrauben befestigt.

Passend zur Halterung habe ich noch einen Endschalter für die Z-Achse entworfen.

item.title: G3 Instant Outlet Mount
item.description:
This is a mount I created that allows a Unifi G3 Instant Camera to cleanly attach directly to an outlet. The pictured USB-C cable is a 6" cable from Amazon. I've included three variants:

-A standard-oriented mount for vertical outlets.
-A sideways-oriented mount for horizontal outlets.
-A nubless mount if you'd prefer to attach the included OEM wall mount with adhesive.

Relay any feedback or suggested changes to /u/DCJodon on reddit.

item.title: Dremel scrollsaw 1800 table inlay
item.description:
Inlay for the Dremel scrollsaw 1800 table.
Original inlay does not fit very well into the saw table (low lying) and has much too large cutouts.
So you can't saw especially smaller parts precisely. They get stuck in the catouts and/or on the passage inlay to the table.

Significant improvement compared to the original inlay, but has still potential for optimization.

item.title: Black Angel Board Game Insert Minor Remix (Split Pieces)
item.description:
I didn't do much here. I just split a few files. I only uploaded the split files so please go see the amazing original design for all the other files (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3869047)

1- The Player Box and lid were one STL. I preferred printing 4 lids at once and 4 box at once. This also give single extruder printers the option to have different color lids.

2- I split the BA_Center_Spacer as it was slightly too big for my printer unless I put it diagonal on the bed which, at least for me, the results are never as good.
